title: BlackBerry Playbook OS 2.1.0.1753 Leak
description:
As usual, neither We, nor Crackberry are responsible for any damage done to your device.
You WILL lose all your data and settings on your device. It will be reset to factory state

BlackBerry PlayBook OS 2.1.0.1753:


The following is a list of found defects or general notices:

General Notice: This is a full OS

General Notice: Functionality wise there is nothing significantly different from the most recent official release. 

General Notice: The OS itself runs a bit smoother, with little to no lag when typing with the keyboard.

General Notice: Browser speed seems to be about the same as previous OSes, still relatively fast 

Issue: After wipe, only end up with browser app
Solution: Run the autoloader again


For FAQ and other helpful information please visit us on our wiki page: *BerryLeaks* or download our app from BlackBerry World: *BerryLeaks Free App*. For personalized help and updates we also have our *Full BerryLeaks App*. And as always, you can contact us in the forum for any needed help.

Device: PlayBook
Device Model: WiFi/WiFi+4G
Issue/Question: Be as specific as possible
What action caused the issue? ie opening X app, turning on X function
What did you try to resolve the issue? ie reboot, reload OS, change settings etc

Questions posted without this information will not be answered by the team.
